			Profile
			
			Dr.WeiLi,professorandASMEFellow,ofEnergyEngineering,ZhejiangUniversity(ZJU),PRChina,hasbeenveryactiveinheatandmasstransfer,airconditioningresearchanddevelopmentfor25yearssinceheobtainedBSinmechanicalengineeringintheXi'anJiaoTongUniversity(XJTU)in1987.WeiLicametotheUnitedStatesin1992tohaveobtainedMSandPh.D.withProf.RalphL.WebbinHeatTransferinthePennsylvaniaStateUniversityin1998.AfterheworkedintheindustryintheUnitedStatesforeightyears,hewashiredasafullprofessorintheDepartmentofEnergyEngineering(ZJU)in2006.HiscorrelationshavebeenincludedintheSectionofTwo-Phaseflowof"2013ASHRAEHandbook-Fundamentals".

Dr.WeiLi’sresearchinenhancedheattransferhasbeenfocusedonoptimizingtheheattransferperformanceofheatexchangersincludingadvancedfingeometries,internaltuberoughness,andothertechniquessuitablefrom-scratchdesignsaswellasin-serviceequipment.Hewasinvolvedinexperimental,numerical,andtheoreticalaspectsofmicro-scaleheatandmassprocess.Hepublishedover110journalpapersandconferencepapers.Dr.Liisrecognizedasaninternationalleaderinmiro-enhancedheattransfer.HemadepresentationsandseminarsatdozensoftopuniversitiesinChina,andMIT,Stanford,UniversityofMaryland,PennState,UniversityofHouston,HongKongPolytechnicUniversity,UniversityofToronto,andsooninrecentyears.Especially,hewasinvitedtobeaplenaryspeakertodeliveraconferencekeynotetwiceatthe2007and2009ChineseNationalHeatTransferConference,respectively.HisMastergraduateobtainedfullscholarshipandcontinuedPh.D.studyinDepartmentofMechanicalEngineeringatMITinUS;HisDoctorgraduateobtainedafacultyofferasassistantprofessorinDepartmentofEnergyEngineeringatLundUniversityinSweden.Hehasbeenaregionaleditor-JournalofEnhancedHeatTransfersince2007.
